{"type":"message","id":"4f3e4b73","parentId":"78c56bd2","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:59:51.251Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 20:59 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Investigate Integration Procedures for OpenClaw Skills\n\n## CONTEXT\nI need to research and document REAL integration procedures for OpenClaw skills. The goal is to understand how skills should actually integrate with each other in production.\n\n## SPECIFIC RESEARCH QUESTIONS:\n\n### 1. Current Integration Patterns\n- What integration patterns currently exist between OpenClaw skills?\n- How do skills communicate with each other (subprocess calls, API, shared files)?\n- What are the success/failure rates of current integrations?\n\n### 2. Best Practices for Skill Integration\n- What are the recommended patterns for skill-to-skill communication?\n- How should error handling work between integrated skills?\n- What about data passing and state management?\n\n### 3. Real Integration Examples\n- Find REAL examples of working integrations in the workspace\n- Document how `salesforce-architect` integrates with `salesforce-code-auditor`\n- Document how `error-learning-loop` integrates with other skills\n\n### 4. Gaps and Recommendations\n- Identify gaps in current integration capabilities\n- Recommend specific improvements\n- Create a simple integration test to validate findings\n\n## DELIVERABLES:\n1. **Research report** with findings on current integration patterns\n2. **Best practices document** for skill integration\n3. **Real integration examples** from workspace\n4. **Gap analysis** and recommendations\n5. **Simple integration test** to validate a working integration\n\n## METHODOLOGY:\n- Examine existing skill code for integration patterns\n- Check documentation and comments\n- Look for actual working examples\n- Test simple integration scenarios\n\n## TIMELINE: 15-20 minutes\n- Research: 10 minutes\n- Documentation: 5 minutes\n- Test creation: 5 minutes\n\n## IMPORTANT: This is a REAL task for testing agent-watchdog monitoring\n- I will be running for 15-20 minutes\n- agent-watchdog should detect and monitor this session\n- Dashboard should show this session as active\n\nProceed with the research."}],"timestamp":1773107991249}}
