{"type":"message","id":"dcd73c83","parentId":"7c9e5ddb","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:00:19.399Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_epDuew3H2d8e35xvwXKw34x4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: REAL monitoring of running agents with actual observability. Detects stalls based on real session data, performs automatic recovery, and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure, observable logs, and integration with OpenClaw ecosystem.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\n**REAL monitoring system** with actual observability of OpenClaw sessions. Monitors real agent sessions from multiple sources, detects stalls based on actual inactivity metrics, performs staged recovery, and reports incidents to error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure with observable logs and artifacts.\n\n## REAL Monitoring Infrastructure\nThe watchdog now has actual monitoring infrastructure:\n\n1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n2. **Real Session Discovery**: Monitors actual OpenClaw sessions from:\n   - `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`\n   - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`\n3. **Observable Logs**: Real monitoring logs with timestamps and session data\n4. **Session Registry**: Persistent tracking of all monitored sessions\n5. **Metrics Collection**: Runtime metrics and recovery statistics\n\n## Key Improvements (From PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL)\n- ✅ **Real monitoring infrastructure** created and working\n- ✅ **Real session discovery** from actual OpenClaw session files\n- ✅ **Observable monitoring logs** with real data (not simulated)\n- ✅ **Real stall detection** based on actual inactivity metrics\n- ✅ **Real recovery triggers** based on monitoring data\n- ✅ **Integration with error-learning-loop** for incident reporting\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks (>5 minutes)\n- Multi-agent workflows with dependencies\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n- Any task requiring real observability\n- When you need to monitor actual OpenClaw session state\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n- Tasks under 2 minutes duration\n\n## REAL Monitoring System Components\n\n### 1. Real Session Monitor (`watchdog_monitor_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Discovers and monitors real OpenClaw sessions\n- **Sources**: \n  - Main agent sessions (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`)\n  - Active sessions (`~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`)\n- **Features**:\n  - Real session discovery and registration\n  - Activity tracking with timestamps\n  - Stall detection based on actual inactivity\n  - Persistent session registry\n  - Observable monitoring logs\n\n### 2. Real Recovery System (`watchdog_recovery_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Triggers recovery based on REAL monitoring data\n- **Features**:\n  - Recovery decisions based on actual inactivity metrics\n  - Staged recovery (nudge → cancel → relaunch)\n  - Incident emission to error-learning-loop\n  - Recovery history tracking\n  - Observable recovery logs\n\n### 3. Integration System (`watchdog_integration.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Connects monitoring and recovery with OpenClaw ecosystem\n- **Features**:\n  - Ecosystem status checking\n  - Operational metrics emission\n  - Self-registration with watchdog\n  - Integration testing\n\n### 4. Configuration (`config/watchdog_config.yaml`)\n- **Purpose**: Centralized configuration for real monitoring\n- **Features**:\n  - Monitoring intervals and timeouts\n  - Recovery escalation settings\n  - Ecosystem integration settings\n  - Testing and validation criteria\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## REAL Monitoring Instructions\n\n[171 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108019394}}
