{"type":"message","id":"14e2918f","parentId":"5e606bc6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:00:25.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Z72LB8pz0u5dAB3asiKGhIaf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## REAL Monitoring Instructions\n\n### Quick Start\n```bash\n# Start the real monitoring system\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --start\n\n# Check status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --status\n\n# Run integration test\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --test\n```\n\n### Manual Monitoring\n```bash\n# Discover and monitor sessions\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --start --duration 300\n\n# Check for stalls\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --check-stalls\n\n# Show monitoring status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --status\n```\n\n### Manual Recovery\n```bash\n# Run recovery cycle\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --run-cycle\n\n# Check if recovery needed\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --check\n\n# Show recovery history\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --history\n```\n\n### Monitoring Workflow\n1. **Session Discovery**: System automatically discovers OpenClaw sessions from multiple sources\n2. **Activity Tracking**: Real-time tracking of session activity based on actual timestamps\n3. **Stall Detection**: Detects stalls when inactivity exceeds configured timeout (default: 120s)\n4. **Recovery Trigger**: Recovery system triggers based on REAL monitoring data (not simulated)\n5. **Incident Emission**: Structured incidents emitted to error-learning-loop with real evidence\n\n### Integration with OpenClaw Ecosystem\n1. **Error-Learning-Loop**: Incidents automatically emitted for processing\n2. **Workspace Janitor**: Log cleanup integrated (7-day retention)\n3. **Observable Artifacts**: All monitoring data stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n\n## Evidence of REAL Monitoring (Anti-Simulation)\n\n### Observable Artifacts\nThe following artifacts prove real monitoring (not simulated):\n\n1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n   - Created and populated with real data\n   - Contains logs, registry, metrics, incidents\n\n2. **Real Session Data**: \n   - `session_registry.json` - Real session IDs from actual OpenClaw\n   - `metrics.json` - Runtime metrics from actual monitoring\n   - `monitoring.log` - Timestamped monitoring activity\n\n3. **Recovery Evidence**:\n   - `recovery.log` - Real recovery attempts with timestamps\n   - `incidents.json` - Structured incidents for error-learning-loop\n   - `operational_metrics.json` - Integration system metrics\n\n4. **Integration Evidence**:\n   - `integration.log` - Ecosystem integration activity\n   - `integration_registry.json` - System registration data\n\n### Test Scenarios (Proven)\n1. **Monitoring Reality Test**: Real sessions discovered and monitored\n2. **Stall Detection Test**: Stalls detected based on actual inactivity\n3. **Recovery Trigger Test**: Recovery triggered by real monitoring data\n4. **Integration Test**: Incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts per session\n- Never restart agents indefinitely\n- Always emit incident report with real evidence\n- Monitor own resource usage (self-protection)\n- Respect session privacy and boundaries\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n\n[72 more lines in file. Use offset=200 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108025853}}
