{"type":"message","id":"d9c94b53","parentId":"dad36404","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:00:33.520Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_dQfu8MR0nsEBKgPHkdNsuFpv","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: salesforce-architect\ndescription: Production-ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: salesforce-architect\n---\n\n# Salesforce Architect Skill\n\n## Overview\nA production‑ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\n\n## CRITICAL RULE – USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe skill must read and consult the following reference PDFs (located in `<workspace>/references/`) before generating any output artifacts:\n\n1. `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` – defines the structure of the Functional Design document.\n2. `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` – defines the structure and fields of the FIT/GAP matrix.\n3. `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` – example of a completed functional design.\n4. `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` – example data model structure.\n\nIf any of these documents are missing, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location\n\n## HARDENED GOVERNANCE REFERENCES (NEW)\nThe skill must also consult the following governance references (located in `skills/salesforce-architect/references/`):\n\n1. `SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md` – stable role definitions and boundaries\n2. `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md` – rules for assigning specialist roles\n3. `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md` – completion criteria per role\n4. `SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md` – project lifecycle states\n5. `ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md` – standardized review process\n6. `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md` – architect ↔ auditor governance\n\nThese are **reference assets, not runtime-generated**. The architect must:\n- Select from pre-defined roles, not invent new ones\n- Apply DoD consistently across all specialist work\n- Enforce state machine transitions\n- Follow review protocol for all validations\n- Use appropriate handoff modes with code auditor\n\n## Salesforce Documentation Evidence Policy\nAllowed domains:\n- `help.salesforce.com`\n- `developer.salesforce.com`\n- `architect.salesforce.com`\n- `trailhead.salesforce.com`\n\nEvery architecture decision must include a reference link to official Salesforce documentation. If evidence cannot be found:\n\n[486 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108033518}}
